    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for the discerning driver is this 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Titanium Silver. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, a masterpiece of engineering featuring individual throttle bodies and high-pressure dual-VANOS variable valve timing. This unit is paired with a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox, delivering power to the rear wheels via a GKN variable M differential lock. Significant preventative maintenance has been performed to ensure chassis longevity, including structural subframe reinforcement and a top-end VANOS service. The suspension geometry remains true to factory specifications, providing the telepathic steering feedback this chassis is renowned for. While the exterior exhibits minor road-going patina, the mechanical synchronization and high-revving acoustics remain impeccable. This is a robust, driver-grade example of one of the finest analog sports coupes ever produced.",
